dal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 17, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jbd1665702548027.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jbd1665702548027.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jbd1665702548027.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jbd1665702548027\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Pathscrambler\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"jbd1665702548027__pathscrambler_124417\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Pathscrambler is command-line utility for encrypting sensitive information and values in assignment files and login strings. These may be used in assignment files, servlet settings, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> ProcScript statement and the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/log</span> (login) command line switch. Uniface automatically decrypts any data that has been encrypted with the Pathscrambler.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jbd1665702548027__p_d39785e1_d39786e1_d39787e1\">In Uniface, path definitions and other settings can contain sensitive information such as server names, port numbers, and user and password combinations required to log on to a network or database. This is useful for providing automatic logon to required data sources, but represents a security risk because the information is clearly visible as ASCII text in assignment files and unsecured connections.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jbd1665702548027__p_d39788e1_d39789e1_d39790e1\">As its name implies, Pathscrambler was originally\n      designed to obfuscate path specifications used for automatic logon to resources.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jbd1665702548027__p_d39791e1_d39792e1_d39793e1\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">pathscrambler.exe</span> executable takes an assignment file, text string, or path definition as input, and returns an assignment file or string in which specific data is encrypted and/or encoded. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dcq1665702522430.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dcq1665702522430.html\" title=\"The pathscrambler.exe executable is used to protect sensitive information such as paths, connection strings, logon information and logicals in Uniface assignment files, Java Servlet settings, and the ProcScript open command.\">pathscrambler.exe</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"jbd1665702548027__note_xdh_s15_zgc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The assignment files the Pathscrambler generates cannot be used by a\n      Uniface application if $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING is set to TRUE — regardless of whether it is\n      defined in the encrypted assignment file, usys.asn, or in any other included file.</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dcq1665702522430.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>pathscrambler.exe</a><p>The pathscrambler.exe executable is used to protect sensitive information such as paths, connection strings, logon information and logicals in Uniface assignment files, Java Servlet settings, and the ProcScript open command.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hot1665702522640.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Encrypting Paths and Other Sensitive Data Using PathScrambler</a><p>Use the Pathscrambler to encrypt logon strings and other sensitive information in assignment files, servlet settings, the open ProcScript command, and the /log (login) command line switch.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528783\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528783\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Pathscrambler Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 17, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Pathscrambler The Pathscrambler is command-line utility for encrypting sensitive information and values in assignment files and login strings. These may be used in assignment files, servlet settings, the open ProcScript statement and the /log (login) command line switch. Uniface automatically decrypts any data that has been encrypted with the Pathscrambler. In Uniface, path definitions and other settings can contain sensitive information such as server names, port numbers, and user and password combinations required to log on to a network or database. This is useful for providing automatic logon to required data sources, but represents a security risk because the information is clearly visible as ASCII text in assignment files and unsecured connections. As its name implies, Pathscrambler was originally designed to obfuscate path specifications used for automatic logon to resources. The pathscrambler.exe executable takes an assignment file, text string, or path definition as input, and returns an assignment file or string in which specific data is encrypted and/or encoded. For more information, see pathscrambler.exe . Note: The assignment files the Pathscrambler generates cannot be used by a Uniface application if $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING is set to TRUE — regardless of whether it is defined in the encrypted assignment file, usys.asn, or in any other included file. Related Links pathscrambler.exe The pathscrambler.exe executable is used to protect sensitive information such as paths, connection strings, logon information and logicals in Uniface assignment files, Java Servlet settings, and the ProcScript open command. Encrypting Paths and Other Sensitive Data Using PathScrambler Use the Pathscrambler to encrypt logon strings and other sensitive information in assignment files, servlet settings, the open ProcScript command, and the /log (login) command line switch. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}